<subSubSection id="0EFC0B699077797075F1EB750709C48B" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="BC66C01E5936CF20E9CAED8F08C7DA1A" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="46AD195683C5264CF3CD13FBF625D107" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">
<bibRefCitation id="C77D7C1CAB953D61CDC5C292307BA1FB" author="de Beaumont, J" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" pagination="211 - 238" publicationUrl="http://researcharchive.calacademy.org/research/entomology/Entomology_Resources/Hymenoptera/sphecidae/copies/Beaumont-1952d.pdf" refId="B10" refString="de Beaumont, J, 1952a. Les Hoplisoides et les Psammaecius de la region palearctique (Hym. Sphecid). Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 25: 211 - 238, http://researcharchive.calacademy.org/research/entomology/Entomology_Resources/Hymenoptera/sphecidae/copies/Beaumont-1952d.pdf" title="Les Hoplisoides et les Psammaecius de la region palearctique (Hym. Sphecid)." url="http://researcharchive.calacademy.org/research/entomology/Entomology_Resources/Hymenoptera/sphecidae/copies/Beaumont-1952d.pdf" volume="25" year="1952 a">De Beaumont (1952a</bibRefCitation>
: 223) changed the state of 
<taxonomicName id="66A9B4786B9278D853A21424FC7457B2" authorityName="de Beaumont" authorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Gorytes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gorytes merceti" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merceti">
<emphasis id="A933F3A8DCE73E2F5ACA0EF64C686C3B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">Gorytes merceti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
de Beaumont to rank of subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="2402ECAEDF14F6CDAFB613634552D0B3" baseAuthorityName="A. Costa" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Hoplisoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hoplisoides craverii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="craverii">
<emphasis id="3D0558C24665B0E807275F462B6C365B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="213">Hoplisoides craverii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(A. Costa). As the only differences between these forms, he cited coloring features of the clypeus and legs. The study of the material from Spain, Russia (Crimea, Dagestan), Azerbaijan, Turkey, Turkmenistan, Uzbekistan and Kazakhstan showed a high variability of these characteristics. We consider 
<taxonomicName id="88B15876B958960580EE582B89F701BD" baseAuthorityName="de Beaumont" baseAuthorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Hoplisoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="subsp. merceti" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="craverii" subSpecies="merceti">ssp. merceti</taxonomicName>
de Beaumont is only a color variation of a rather variable species with a range of color geographic forms.
</paragraph>
